According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Battery Vent Cap Market was valued at USD 1,415 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1,528 million in 2025 to USD 2,516 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 8.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth due to the rapid expansion of electric vehicle (EV) production, increasing deployment of large-scale energy storage systems, and tightening global battery safety regulations. Battery vent caps have become essential safety components in lithium-ion and lead-acid batteries, helping regulate internal pressure, safely release gases, and prevent thermal runaway incidents that could compromise battery performance and user safety.
As the global automotive industry accelerates its transition toward electrification, demand for advanced battery safety technologies continues to rise. Battery vent caps play a critical role in maintaining battery integrity by controlling internal pressure generated during charging, discharging, and extreme operating conditions. Leading electric vehicle manufacturers are increasingly adopting high-performance vent caps with enhanced pressure tolerance and improved thermal management capabilities to comply with evolving international safety standards and improve battery reliability.
